.TH _PRINTF 1 "07 October 2021" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
_printf - prints data and also it formats data.
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

.B "PRINTF"
.SH DESCRIPTION

The printf() function formats and prints a series of characters and values. Format specifications, beginning with a percent sign (%), determine the output format for any argument-list following the format-string.

_printf will take variable arguments.

Example:
_printf("%s", text);

the above syntax is saying "print the value of text as %s gives the format of text".

.B conversion specifiers

-specifies whether to interpret the corresponding argument as a character, a string, a pointer, an integer, or a floating-point number.

.IP %c
- prints character.
.IP %s
- prints string.
.IP %%
- prints percentage symbol.
.IP %d
- prints decimal.
.IP %i
- prints integer number.

